Approximation of trawled volume. Assumed trawl to be spherical (only vertical height 4-6 m given) towed for an average of 3 nm = 5556 m.

Calculated area based off of the assumption that all samples were 150 m long plankton tows, and that there were equal shallow and deep water tows in both years. Only one year had comparable plot size.

What counts as an event? Resampling was done in 2006 to look for evidence of a change in community composition either 'natural' or climate driven. 1997 was used as the 'start' year because it looks like values for richness and Shannon were taken as the average of samples from 1997 and 1998. See data acquisition protocol. 1997/1998 data consists of 24 stations sampled with 3 replicate Van Veen grabs each. This is why n is so large for 1997.
